<td align="left">A failure in the RG MUST NOT affect the private intra-premises network
except for those functions provided by the RG (e.g. DHCP, DNS, L2
bridging).</td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td align="left"><span id="req:if.wan.xdsl.3">IF.WAN.xDSL.3<a class="headerlink" href="#req:if.wan.xdsl.3" title="Permalink to this span"> <img src='permalink.png' title='' width="0.8em"/></a></span></td>
<td align="left">The RG MUST NOT cause any failure in or interference with the xDSL
network.</td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td align="left"><span id="req:if.wan.xdsl.4">IF.WAN.xDSL.4<a class="headerlink" href="#req:if.wan.xdsl.4" title="Permalink to this span"> <img src='permalink.png' title='' width="0.8em"/></a></span></td>
<td align="left">Failure or removal of LAN CPE connected to the DSL RG MUST NOT prevent
