<h1 class="appendix new-page appendix1" id="sec:sealing-current-references">Appendix V: Sealing Current References<a class="headerlink" href="#sec:sealing-current-references" title="Permalink to this header"> <img src='permalink.png' title='' width="0.8em"/></a></h1>

<p>Sealing current is also known in the telecommunications industry as
wetting current. Sealing current may be sourced by the ATU-C in certain
service providers that deploy &ldquo;dry loop&rdquo; DSL circuits, meaning that DSL
is delivered in the absence of typical central office or remote terminal
fed analog POTS service on the copper pair.</p>

